# Todo App — Project Config

## Tech Stack

| Layer | Technology |
|-------|------------|
| Frontend | React 18, TypeScript, Vite, Vitest, Testing Library |
| Backend | Spring Boot 3.2, Java 17, Spring Data JPA |
| Database | H2 in-memory |
| Package managers | npm (frontend), Maven (backend) |

## Folder Structure

```
workspace/
├── backend/                    # Spring Boot
│   ├── src/main/java/com/example/todo/
│   │   ├── Todo.java           # JPA entity
│   │   ├── TodoRepository.java # JPA repository
│   │   ├── TodoController.java # REST controller
│   │   └── TodoApplication.java
│   ├── src/main/resources/
│   │   └── application.properties
│   └── pom.xml
├── frontend/                   # React + Vite
│   ├── src/
│   │   ├── App.tsx
│   │   ├── api.ts              # API client (base: http://localhost:8080/api)
│   │   ├── types.ts
│   │   └── test/setup.ts
│   ├── package.json
│   └── vite.config.ts
└── crew-ai/feature-todo-app/   # Plans, specs (gitignored)
```

## Common Commands

| Action | Command |
|--------|---------|
| Backend: run | `cd backend && ./mvnw spring-boot:run` or `mvn spring-boot:run` |
| Backend: test | `cd backend && mvn test` |
| Backend: build | `cd backend && mvn package` |
| Frontend: dev | `cd frontend && npm run dev` |
| Frontend: build | `cd frontend && npm run build` |
| Frontend: test | `cd frontend && npm run test` |

## API Endpoints

| Method | Path | Purpose |
|--------|------|---------|
| GET | /api/todos | List all todos |
| POST | /api/todos | Create todo (body: `{ "title": "..." }`) |
| PATCH | /api/todos/{id} | Update todo (partial body) |
| DELETE | /api/todos/{id} | Delete todo |

## Key Types

- **Todo**: `id` (number), `title` (string), `completed` (boolean)
- Backend entity: `com.example.todo.Todo` (JPA)
- Frontend type: `src/types.ts` `Todo` interface

## Rules and Constraints

- Do NOT add auth, filtering, sorting, or persistence beyond in-memory
- Do NOT modify test files — they are the oracle
- Backend port: 8080; frontend dev server: Vite default (5173)
- CORS must be enabled for frontend to call backend
